National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) Director General Yukiya Amano at the White House. They discussed the United States' commitment to the IAEA and its important role in promoting international security and the peaceful use of nuclear energy. Rice expressed appreciation for the IAEA's work in verifying Iran's compliance under the Joint Plan of Action and expressed confidence in their ability to effectively verify the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA). The JCPOA aims to prevent Iran from acquiring a nuclear weapon. They also discussed the IAEA's investigation into the possible military dimensions of Iran's nuclear program, and Rice emphasized the US government's support in addressing all outstanding questions. Rice assured Amano that the US and its partners would provide the necessary resources for the IAEA to carry out its mission effectively.